@TheBlueMatt Not sure about pull-tester. Travis uses the same as Gitian.

@ENikS we don't target any toolchains, but we do test and support-ish some. Due to the nature of Bitcoin, most devs work in Linux, some in OSX, some in the BSDs, and few in Windows. Official builds must be created using an entirely free/open stack, including the toolchain. mingw is much easier to automate for c-i and deployments, so it's the obvious choice for us.

However, there's no reason why the code shouldn't build under MSVC.  Any build failure (assuming it's caused by non-conformant code as opposed to a MSVC quirk) is a bug and should be fixed.
